						               													<description>This is a fantasy themed 4-player version of MetaCheckers: Battlefield with all-wood, laser cut pieces. Play as one of four ancient gods:&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Zeus / Greek temples&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Odin / viking ships&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Amun-Ra / sphinxes&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Marduk / Babylonian ziggurats&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player gets 6 board tiles - four squares each - which they take turns placing on the field of play, connecting the tiles to form a unique battlefield.  Players place their 12 checkers strategically on the squares of their tiles, with the kings hidden, face down at the beginning of the game. Eliminate your opponents by capturing their god / king.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On their turn, players roll two dice to determine how to move a checker. One die has the symbols for chess pieces, the other is a standard d6 numbers die.  Whenever a 6 is rolled, the player may opt to reroll with the HERO Die and the numbers die for 6 additional useful moves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players eliminate their opponents by capturing the hidden god / king of the opposing army, which then leaves the board. Last player standing wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
